node.text:
Today at 12 PM, we will sell Hydrophilic (8.5% DIPA) at $ 20 per 4-PK, no limit. We will have this available at the brewery or delivery throughout New York, Pennsylvania, Washington D.C., Ohio, Nevada, New Hampshire, Vermont, North Dakota, Kentucky, Nebraska, and Virginia! (Please follow individual State limits for delivery)
Hydrophilic literally means “water love”. A hydrophilic molecule has more favorable thermodynamic interactions with polar solvents vs non polar solvents, which means yummy compounds will stay in the beer verses sorbing and settling with yeast or volatizing out of the fermentor during fermentation. This beer utilizes a new product from Yakima Chief Hops, which is a Cryo Survivables hop blend. We used this blend in the whirlpool which allows the yummy hop compounds to end up in your glass instead of making great tasting yeast or the refreshing the brewery air.
Starting off with flaked oats and wheat we used YCH cyro survivables hop blend and then dry hopped with Citra and Rakau. Pouring a hazy and straw yellow we get aromas of citrus, passionfruit, and melon with deep flavors of candied orange, passionfruit, cantaloupe, peach, apricot, and a touch of berry packed into a luscious mouthfeel with a creamy and explosive #🌈🍈 #EQjuice finish.

Have you visited yet?

Two of our passions under one roof. @eqbonfire Barbecue prepared on our Lang smoker and craft beer we have been proudly making in Middletown, NY since 2016.

We are here 7 days a week serving beer and food for onsite enjoyment in our taproom or beer garden.

node.text:
Help us welcome Keaton to the production side of our ops. Keaton started at EQ in January of 2021 on the canning line helping us get our beer packaged.
Being a home brewer, he always showed an interest and curiosity in everything that goes into brewing a batch of beer on a production system. We love passion and promoting from within when possible and we are happy to have Keaton training under Mikey this week for his new cellar position. 🎉

node.text:
Today at 12PM, we will sell, Galaxy Flare (8.5 % DIPA) $20 per 4-PK, no limit. We will have this available with options for curbside pickup at the brewery or delivery throughout New York, Pennsylvania, Washington D.C., Ohio, Nevada, New Hampshire, Vermont, North Dakota, Nebraska, Kentucky, and Virginia! (Please follow individual State limits for delivery)
Our all Galaxy DIPA and its explosive fruit forward flavor is named after the byproduct of our Galaxy’s explosion. This cataclysmic space event and flare punched outward in both directions from our galaxy’s center and reached so far into intergalactic space that its impact was felt 200,000 light-years away. 
Galaxy Flare starts off with a base of white wheat and flaked oats, we used our 100% hand selected Victorian Galaxy in both the whirlpool and dry hop for the hop bill. Pouring a deep hazy yellow, saturated aromas and flavors of Florida navel orange, passionfruit, lychee, and grapefruit build into a dank #EQjuice forward finish with a balanced creaminess and a touch of hop bitterness.

node.text:
This Wednesday, 7/21/21 at 9am on Eventbrite and this Saturday, 7/24/21 at 11am at Retail, we will sell Macademics (11% ABV Imperial Stout) a collab with @greatnotion $20 per 500 ML bottle. Limit 6 bottles per person. Proxies welcome. Please add Eventbrite confirmation to Pickup or Delivery orders when checking out on our website. No Minimum order for shipping bottles to NY, PA, D.C, OH, VT, ND, NV, NH, KY. NE or VA but please keep in mind the flat rate is in place based on your location. Claim by 7/28/21 and please add Eventbrite order number while checking out on our website. 

Macademics will be on Nitro this Saturday at 11am when the taproom opens!

Macadamia Nuts, Academics, Beavers, Owls, and all in athletic track suits calculating a thicc stout: Macademics… We took out our Texas Instruments TI-81 calculators with our pals from Oregon to figure out the max amount of Macadamia nuts, Coconut, Cacao, and Madagascar vanilla beans possible in our latest stout. This viscous liquid pours pitch black with a mocha head exploding with an aroma macadamia cookies dunked into a salted caramel frap. This absolute big body stout has liquid velvet flavors of macadamia and chocolate chip cookies, Almond Joy bars drizzled with caramel in a thicccc finish that rolls around your palate before making its way to your belly like the most decadent dessert.

node.text:
With the unrelenting drive to make each batch better than the last, we have been working hard in the lab to bring you the best of our Rainbow Melon #🌈🍈 #EQjuice profile.
Today we bring you a batch of Fluctuation Wave we are especially proud of. Using our hand selected Citra from several farms across the Pacific North West, Fluctuation Wave takes our beloved DIPA Fluctuation, supersizes the hop bill, adds a touch of lactose, and uses our latest hop process. A DIPA version of Straight Outta The Laboratory, this batch exhibits giant peach notes with ripe drippy honeydew melon in an absolutely stunning escalation of flavors that can be enjoyed from a glass or a straw.

Fluctuation Wave (8.5% DIPA) will be available with options for pickup at the brewery or delivery throughout New York, Washington D.C., Ohio, Nevada, New Hampshire, Vermont, North Dakota, Nebraska, Kentucky, Pennsylvania, and Virginia today.

node.text:
Today, we will sell, Bitrate Fluctuation Batch 2, a collaboration with @weldwerksbrewing (8.5% ABV DIPA) at $20 per 4-pk, no limit. We will have this available with options for curbside pickup at the brewery or delivery throughout New York, Washington D.C., Ohio, Nevada, New Hampshire, Vermont, and North Dakota, Pennsylvania, and Virginia.

Taking inspiration from the Weldworks Bits beer series and our beer, Fluctuation, we fused the two to create Bitrate Fluctuation. A bitrate is the number of bits per second that can be transmitted along a digital network. These fluctuations in transmission describe the rate at which bits are transferred from one location to another. In other words, it measures how much hoppy goodness is transmitted to your palate in a given amount of time.
We took our Fluctuation base added lots of Oats and Wheat and combined it Citra whirlpool and a dry hop of Citra, Strata, Lotus and BRU-1. Bitrate Fluctuation pours a hazy tangerine and has citrus and floral aroma with flavors of tropical orange, papaya, rich saturated pineapple, and bright berries in a creamy #EQjuice finish with just a touch of bite that will keep your brain BPS (Bits Per Second) flowing freely with each sip!

At 12PM today, we will sell, Harvester of Simcoe (8.8% DIPA) at $20 per 4-pk (No Limit). We will have this available with options for curbside pickup at the brewery or delivery throughout New York, Washington D.C., Ohio, Nevada, New Hampshire, Vermont, and North Dakota, Pennsylvania, and Virginia.
Using our hand selected Simcoe, Harvester of Simcoe has aromas of passion fruit, peach flesh, melon, bright pine, berry and earth, followed by some bready notes. The taste is light pine and tropical fruits supported by a firm but rounded bitterness and our #EQjuice finish.
